dc_title_s: Pitman East Quadrangle, New Jersey, 7.5 minute series (topographic)
dc_description_s: U.S.G.S. 7.5 minute series (topographic) North Decimal Degree 39.750000. South Decimal Degree 39.625000. East Decimal Degree -75.000000. West Decimal Degree -75.125000. Alternate title: Pitman East, N. J. Polyconic projection. Universal transverse Mercator grids are shown. Relief shown by 10 feet contour interval and spot heights. Datum is mean sea level. "Mapped, edited, and published by the United States Geological Survey. Control by USGS, USC&GS, and New Jersey Geogetic Survey. Planimetry by photogrammetric methods from aerial photographs taken 1951. Topography by plantable surveys 1953. Revised 1966." Map is temporarily filed in the Reserve Course Materials Collection.
